    "bbox": [
      86.18,
      318.51,
      527.14,
      332.51
    ],
    "text": "4. Contumacious conduct refers to behaviour that is deliberately",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      339.63,
      527.17,
      353.63
    ],
    "text": "disobedient or rebellious, particularly in a legal or authoritative context.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      360.75,
      527.07,
      374.75
    ],
    "text": "In legal proceedings, such conduct often manifests as contempt of",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      381.87,
      527.24,
      395.87
    ],
    "text": "Court, where an individual wilfully disregards the Court\u2019s authority,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      403.01,
      245.69,
      417.01
    ],
    "text": "orders or proceedings.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      86.18,
      445.37,
      527.05,
      459.37
    ],
    "text": "5. Such behaviour can undermine the rule of law and the administration",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      466.49,
      527.28,
      480.49
    ],
    "text": "of justice. For instance, a person who refuses to comply with a Court",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      487.61,
      527.18,
      501.61
    ],
    "text": "order, such as failing to provide necessary documents or not attending",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      508.73,
      527.19,
      522.73
    ],
    "text": "a scheduled hearing, exhibits contumacious conduct. This defiance not",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      529.85,
      527.18,
      543.85
    ],
    "text": "only disrupts the legal process but also poses challenges for judges and",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      550.97,
      378.67,
      564.97
    ],
    "text": "legal practitioners striving to uphold the law.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      86.18,
      572.12,
      527.25,
      600.16
    ],
    "text": "6. The appellant, by absconding from Court, has wilfully disregarded the",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      607.4,
      527.11,
      621.4
    ],
    "text": "Magistrates Court\u2019s authority. The conduct undermines the rule of law",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      628.52,
      527.04,
      642.52
    ],
    "text": "and obstructs the proper administration of justice. It amounts to",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      649.64,
      527.24,
      663.64
    ],
    "text": "contumacious behaviour, a deliberate and defiant refusal to comply",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      670.76,
      527.17,
      684.76
    ],
    "text": "with the Magistrates Court\u2019s processes and orders. By choosing to evade",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      691.88,
      527.19,
      705.88
    ],
    "text": "the Court rather than participate in the proceedings, the appellant has",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      713.0,
      527.05,
      727.0
    ],
    "text": "placed himself beyond the reach of the legal process and has shown",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      734.14,
      344.83,
      748.14
    ],
    "text": "open disrespect for the judicial system.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      777.82,
      527.52,
      806.4
    ],
    "text": "4",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold",
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      86.18,
      72.0,
      527.18,
      86.0
    ],
    "text": "7. Absconding is not a mere procedural lapse or misunderstanding. It is a",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      93.12,
      527.17,
      107.12
    ],
    "text": "conscious act that frustrates the Court\u2019s ability to manage the case",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      114.24,
      527.13,
      128.24
    ],
    "text": "efficiently. It also creates practical prejudice including delay, increased",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      135.36,
      527.14,
      149.36
    ],
    "text": "costs, and difficulty in enforcing orders, all of which impair public",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      156.48,
      527.22,
      170.48
    ],
    "text": "confidence in the justice system. Such behaviour is properly",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      177.6,
      527.1,
      191.6
    ],
    "text": "characterized as contumacious because, it reflects wilful disobedience",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      198.72,
      465.82,
      212.72
    ],
    "text": "and an attitude of defiance towards the authority of Courts.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      86.18,
      241.11,
      527.15,
      255.11
    ],
    "text": "8. In these circumstances, the appellant could not have reasonably sought",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      262.23,
      527.28,
      276.23
    ],
    "text": "the High Court\u2019s assistance by way of discretionary relief, while",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      283.35,
      527.27,
      297.35
    ],
    "text": "simultaneously refusing to submit to the Magistrates Court\u2019s",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
